7.4:
Your neck — white as an ivory tower;
your eyes, still as the pools of Heshbon by the city gate of Bath-rabbim;
your nose, proud as the tower of Lebanon gazing out toward Damascus.

7.5:
Your head rises upon you like Mount Carmel's crown;
your flowing locks shimmer like royal purple —
a king himself is ensnared in your tresses.

7.13:
The mandrakes breathe out their fragrance;
all manner of choice fruit waits at our door —
old vintages and new, every treasure I have laid in store for you, my love.
